radiographic_examinations.findings: Small anterior pituitary, absent pituitary stalk with an undescended or ectopic posterior pituitary at the tuber cinereum, and thin corpus callosum
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: At 2 months of age revealed a thin corpus callosum and a cavum septum pellucidum; at 20 months showed a small anterior pituitary and an absent pituitary stalk with an ectopic posterior pituitary.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Generalized white matter loss and midline abnormalities (cavum septum pellucidum and vergae, small anterior pituitary, a single anterior cerebral artery, thin optic chiasm)
